   <abstract>Marion Ruth Spies was born in Ohio on January 22, 1905. She worked as a schoolteacher before moving to Hollywood in search of a more exciting life. She married director Clarence L. Brown on November 10, 1947. He had previously been married to Paul (called Polly) Pratt, Ona Maris, and Alice Joyce. Later in life, Marion Brown became one of the major forces behind the Browns' many contributions to the University of Tennessee. Clarence Brown died on August 17, 1987 and Marion Brown followed on May 10, 1993.</abstract>
